It is not possible to set table name dynamically.You can set dynamically column names.it is not possible to set table name

try like this

    select a.name from &#39;+table name+&#39;where a.id = &#39;2&#39;

In my opinion, There are 2 ways to resolve this issue:

1- If you are using Spring and Hibernate together, you could use [SpEL][1] and it would be like #{#entityName} as it is described [here][2]

```
@Entity
public class User {

  @Id
  @GeneratedValue
  Long id;

  String lastname;
}

public interface UserRepository extends JpaRepository&lt;User,Long&gt; {

  @Query(&quot;select u from #{#entityName} u where u.lastname = ?1&quot;)
  List&lt;User&gt; findByLastname(String lastname);
}
```

2-You could use [CriteriaBuilder][3] like 
```
CriteriaQuery&lt;YourEntity&gt; cr = cb.createQuery(YourEntity.class);
Root&lt;YourEntity&gt; root = cr.from(YourEntity.class);
cr.select(root);
```

I copied the source codes from the provided links and they are described there much better


  [1]: https://docs.spring.io/spring-framework/docs/3.2.x/spring-framework-reference/html/expressions.html
  [2]: https://docs.spring.io/spring-data/data-jpa/docs/1.7.x/reference/html/#jpa.query.spel-expressions
  [3]: https://www.baeldung.com/hibernate-criteria-queries

